Question Text: The command that configures the switch as a DHCP client to discover its IPv4 address, mask, and default gateway is ip address dhcp.
LLM Explanation: The command 'ip address dhcp' is used to configure an interface on a Cisco router, not a switch, to obtain its IPv4 address, subnet mask, and default gateway from a DHCP server. Switches do not typically act as DHCP clients. Instead, they are usually configured with static IP addresses or act as DHCP servers for other devices on the network.
URLs: ['Cisco IOS IP Addressing Services Command Reference: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/ipaddr/command/ipaddr-cr-book/ipaddr-i1.html#wp3782044220', 'Cisco Networking Academy: Introduction to Networks v7.0 (ITN) - Chapter 8: DHCP']
SM - Description: Implied context that question is talking about layer 3 switches. Wrong information because why are switches usually DHCP servers?

Question Text: Which of the following Cisco IOS Software Command Help lists commands that start with int?
Choices:
a. int<Tab>
b. int ?
c. ?
d. int?
LLM Explanation: The correct command to list commands that start with 'int' is 'int ?'. The question mark (?) is used in Cisco IOS Software Command Help to list available commands or command options that begin with the specified prefix, in this case 'int'.
URLs: ['Cisco IOS Command Modes: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/fundamentals/command/Cisco_IOS_Configuration_Fundamentals_Command_Reference/cf_command_ref/cf_a1.html#wp3936003116', 'Cisco IOS Terminal Services Command Reference: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/termserv/command/ts-cr-book/ts-a1.html#wp3151786950']
SM - Description: int? is the right format. With a space, we list all commands that come after int (e.g. parameters)
